				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13022093/scp-5040#post-4854392</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 26 Dec 2020 21:32:21 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Draven Addams</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>7103385</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I&#8230; honestly thought there would be more to it. It had this great build-up, it felt like it was leading to some horrific revelation or something, and then it just&#8230; didn't. I clicked on it because I saw the Castlevania reference in the title, and then it started out <em>really</em> good, like I was genuinely excited about where this was going, and it just went nowhere imo. Sorry, I don't like leaving mean comments, but I'm just really disappointed right now. But it seems like other people liked it a lot, so hey, you still did a good job! Still a -1 from me though :(</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13022093#post-4822475</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13022093/scp-5040#post-4822475</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 19 Nov 2020 15:40:12 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>TL333s</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1304786</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Shoot, this shouldn't be as good as it is. It's just a creepy movie coupled with a shared dream, yet all the details of the people in the theater (plus the excellent plot writing for the movie itself) make this intensely creepy!</p> <p>Or maybe it's just because I was watching a video about supposed lost anime &quot;Saki Sanobashi&quot; earlier today and this hits a lot of similar notes.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
